PARTICIPATIONYou are invited to
participate in an invasive species impacts survey if you are 19 years of age or
older. This project aims to improve our ability to understand how multiple
invasive species are expected to alter valued resources in Nebraska’s
rangelands.   The invasive species
impact survey should take approximately 45 minutes to complete. The survey
consists of a series of questions regarding your familiarity with invasive
species, those species impacts on resources and services provided by Nebraska’s
rangelands, and your personal uncertainty regarding your impact estimate.
Following the survey we will discuss the group’s responses (individual
responses will be kept anonymous) and how they compare with impacts from
scientific studies. Following this discussion, all participants will have the
opportunity to adjust previously provided responses. To re-send participants a
link to their previously completed survey, we ask that you provide your email
address at the beginning of the survey. Your responses will remain anonymous to
other participants. Your participation in
this survey is voluntary and not required to attend this workshop. You can
decide not to be in this research study, or you can stop being in this research
study (withdraw) at any time before, during, or after the research begins for
any reason. Deciding not to be in this research study or deciding to withdraw
will not affect your relationship with the investigator or with the University
of Nebraska-Lincoln. There are no known personal risks or benefits associated
with the invasive species impact survey.  CONFIDENTIALITYYour responses will be
stored and presented as anonymous data. Your results will be sent to Qualtrics
online survey platform where data will be stored in a password protected
electronic format (Qualtrics privacy policies are available at https://www.qualtrics.com/privacy-statement/).
After participants have had the opportunity to alter their responses, all
identifying information will be removed from the data and no one will be able
to identify your responses. At no time will data be presented in a manner that
allows identification of participants. You are encouraged to
ask questions concerning your participation in this research and have those
questions answered before agreeing to participate in the invasive species
impact assessment. For further questions,
please contact Dirac Twidwell at dirac.twidwell@unl.edu
or Dillon Fogarty at dillon.fogarty@huskers.unl.edu.
  For questions
concerning your rights or complaints about the research contact the
Institutional Review Board (IRB) at 1(402)472-6965 or irb@unl.edu.
